25|$|In some {{cultures}} of Asia, a <b>hijra</b> is usually {{considered to be}} neither a man nor a woman. Most are anatomically male or intersex, but some are anatomically female. The <b>hijra</b> form a third gender role, although they do not enjoy the same acceptance and respect as males and females in their cultures. They can run their own households, and their occupations are singing and dancing, working as cooks or servants, sometimes prostitutes, or long-term sexual partners with men. Hijras {{can be compared to}} transvestites or drag queens of contemporary western culture.|$|E
