5000|$|YaPi {{published}} {{their first}} YouTube video [...] "Can you tear up the Tricolour for 1000 INR" [...] on 24 January 2015 {{to celebrate the}} 66th Republic Day of India which was shared by many e-papers and blogs. They created another video titled 'Bharatiya... Hum Bhi Hai' in August, 2015 to celebrate the 69th Independence Day of India {{as well as the}} NALSA Judgement of 2014. The video showed 7 <b>Hijras</b> dressed in outfits or uniforms of various professions and singing the National Anthem of India. The <b>Hijras</b> featured in the video were brought together by the Humsafar Trust, a Mumbai-based NGO which promotes LGBT rights. The video went viral in no time and was featured in all leading news papers, e-papers and blogs in India for being the first National Anthem video sung by <b>Hijras</b> as well as for showing how <b>Hijras</b> would look if they get the chance to take up any dignified career.|$|R
